import { View, Text, Image } from 'react-native'
import React from 'react'
import { Ionicons } from '@expo/vector-icons';


const TuyChon = () => {
    return (
        <View style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#E5E9EB' }}>
            <View style={{ height: 150, backgroundColor: 'purple', justifyContent: 'center', alignItems: 'center', paddingTop: 10, backgroundColor: 'white' }}>
                <Image source={{ uri: 'https://randomuser.me/api/portraits/men/68.jpg' }} style={{ width: 100, height: 100, borderRadius: 50 }} />
                <Text style={{ fontSize: 20, fontWeight: 'bold' }}>Huynh Quoc Hao</Text>
            </View>
            <View style={{ height: 100, backgroundColor: 'white', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center', flexDirection: 'row', paddingHorizontal: 50 }}>
                <View style={{ width: 70, height: 100, backgroundColor: 'purple',justifyContent:'center', alignItems:'center' }}>
                    <Ionicons name="call-outline" size={27} color="white" style={{ padding: 5, paddingStart: 15, marginRight: 10 }} />
                    <Text style={{textAlign:'center'}}>Tìm{'\n'}Tin Nhắn</Text>
                </View>
                <View style={{ width: 70, height: 100, backgroundColor: 'purple' }}></View>
                <View style={{ width: 70, height: 100, backgroundColor: 'purple' }}></View>
                <View style={{ width: 70, height: 100, backgroundColor: 'purple' }}></View>
            </View>

        </View>
    )
}

export default TuyChon
